usdPppProfileMIB.name: usdPppProfileMIB

revisions.description: Added support for negotiation of the IPCP option netmask.
Added support for dynamic multilink PPP (MLPPP) interfaces.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdPppProfileMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdPppProfileMIB.description: The Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) Profile MIB for the Unisphere Netowrks enterprise. This MIB provides configuration parameters that extend the tables found in the Unisphere-Data-PROFILE-MIB to support profiles for PPP interfaces.

usdPppProfileTable.name: usdPppProfileTable
usdPppProfileTable.description: This table contains profiles for configuring PPP interfaces. Entries in this table are created/deleted as a side-effect of corresponding operations to the usdProfileNameTable in the Unisphere-Data-PROFILE-MIB.

usdPppProfileEntry.name: usdPppProfileEntry
usdPppProfileEntry.description: A profile describing configuration of a PPP interface.

usdPppProfileId.name: usdPppProfileId
usdPppProfileId.description: The integer identifier associated with this profile. A value for this identifier is determined by locating or creating a profile name in the Unisphere-Data-PROFILE-MIB.usdProfileNameTable.

usdPppProfileSetMap.name: usdPppProfileSetMap
usdPppProfileSetMap.description: A bitmap representing which objects in this entry have been explicitly configured. See the definition of the UsdSetMap TEXTUAL-CONVENTION for details of use. The INDEX object(s) and this object are excluded from representation (i.e. their bits are never set). When a SET request does not explicitly configure UsdSetMap, bits in UsdSetMap are set as a side-effect of configuring other profile attributes in the same entry. If, however, a SET request explicitly configures UsdSetMap, the explicitly configured value overrides 1) any previous bit settings, and 2) any simultaneous 'side-effect' settings that would otherwise occur. Once set, bits can only be cleared by explicitly configuring UsdSetMap.

usdPppProfileLcpMagicNumber.name: usdPppProfileLcpMagicNumber
usdPppProfileLcpMagicNumber.description: If true(2) then the local node will attempt to perform Magic Number negotiation with the remote node. If false(1) then this negotiation is not performed. In any event, the local node will comply with any magic number negotiations attempted by the remote node, per the PPP specification.

usdPppProfileLcpKeepalive.name: usdPppProfileLcpKeepalive
usdPppProfileLcpKeepalive.description: Keepalive interval in seconds. A value of zero disables keepalive. Keepalive is performed using LCP Echo.

usdPppProfileLcpAuthentication.name: usdPppProfileLcpAuthentication
usdPppProfileLcpAuthentication.description: Specifies the type(s) of authentication, if any, to be negotiated with the peer: none No authentication is negotiated. pap PAP negotiation only. chap CHAP negotiation only. papChap PAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt CHAP. chapPap CHAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt PAP. Setting this object to none will set usdPppProfileAuthenticatorVirtualRouter object to an empty string.

usdPppProfileIpPeerDnsPriority.name: usdPppProfileIpPeerDnsPriority
usdPppProfileIpPeerDnsPriority.description: When enabled, allows peer's DNS address to prevail in the event of a negotiation conflict; when disabled, the local PPP interface's DNS address prevails.

usdPppProfileIpPeerWinsPriority.name: usdPppProfileIpPeerWinsPriority
usdPppProfileIpPeerWinsPriority.description: When enabled, allows peer's WINS address to prevail in the event of a negotiation conflict; when disabled, the local PPP interface's WINS address prevails.

usdPppProfileLcpInitialMRU.name: usdPppProfileLcpInitialMRU
usdPppProfileLcpInitialMRU.description: The initial Maximum Receive Unit (MRU) that the local PPP entity will advertise to the remote entity. If the value of this variable is 1 then the local PPP entity will advertise an MRU value determined by its underlying media interface.

usdPppProfilePacketLog.name: usdPppProfilePacketLog
usdPppProfilePacketLog.description: When enabled, allows packet logging on dynamic PPP interfaces.

usdPppProfileStateLog.name: usdPppProfileStateLog
usdPppProfileStateLog.description: When enabled, allows state machine logging on dynamic PPP interfaces.

usdPppProfileChapMinChallengeLength.name: usdPppProfileChapMinChallengeLength
usdPppProfileChapMinChallengeLength.description: Minimum value of the CHAP authenticator challenge length value. This value is never allowed to be set to a value greater than usdPppProfileChapMaxChallengeLength.

usdPppProfileChapMaxChallengeLength.name: usdPppProfileChapMaxChallengeLength
usdPppProfileChapMaxChallengeLength.description: Maximum value of the CHAP authenticator challenge length value. This value is never allowed to be set to a value less than usdPppLinkConfigChapMinChallengeLength.

usdPppProfilePassiveMode.name: usdPppProfilePassiveMode
usdPppProfilePassiveMode.description: When enabled, LCP state machine is forced into passive mode on lower layer UP message. It adds compatibility with slow and buggy clients.

usdPppProfileMlppp.name: usdPppProfileMlppp
usdPppProfileMlppp.description: Enables the creation of dynamic multi-link PPP interfaces.

usdPppProfileIpcpNetmask.name: usdPppProfileIpcpNetmask
usdPppProfileIpcpNetmask.description: Enables the negotiation of the IPCP option netmask (0x90) during IPCP negotiation.

usdPppProfileAuthenticatorVirtualRouter.name: usdPppProfileAuthenticatorVirtualRouter
usdPppProfileAuthenticatorVirtualRouter.description: The name of the virtual router (Unisphere-Data-ROUTER-MIB.usdRouterName) to be used for authentication on the PPP interface. Setting this object statically binds the authenticating virtual router with the PPP interface. If this object is not explicitly set or it is set to null string, then this object is ignored and the virtual router used for authentication is determined by other means. On a Set operation, if the value of this object is not null and does not correspond to an existing virtual router, then an inconsistentValue error is returned. Setting this object to non null string returns inconsistentValue value error if usdPppProfileConfigAuthentication object is none or not configured.

usdPppProfileCompliance.name: usdPppProfileCompliance
usdPppProfileCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere PPP Profile MIB. This statement became obsolete when support was added for multi-link PPP interfaces.

usdPppProfileCompliance2.name: usdPppProfileCompliance2
usdPppProfileCompliance2.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere PPP Profile MIB. This statement became obsolete when support was added for negotiation of IPCP option netmask.

usdPppProfileCompliance3.name: usdPppProfileCompliance3
usdPppProfileCompliance3.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere PPP Profile MIB. This statement became obsolete when the usdPppProfileAuthenticatorVirtualRouter object was added.

usdPppProfileCompliance4.name: usdPppProfileCompliance4
usdPppProfileCompliance4.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere PPP Profile MIB.

usdPppProfileGroup.name: usdPppProfileGroup
usdPppProfileGroup.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of profile functionality for PPP interfaces in a Unisphere product. This group became obsolete when support was added for MLPPP.

usdPppProfileGroup2.name: usdPppProfileGroup2
usdPppProfileGroup2.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of profile functionality for PPP interfaces in a Unisphere product. This group became obsolete when support was added for negotiation of IPCP option netmask.

usdPppProfileGroup3.name: usdPppProfileGroup3
usdPppProfileGroup3.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of profile functionality for PPP interfaces in a Unisphere product. This group became obsolete when the usdPppProfileAuthenticatorVirtualRouter object was added.

usdPppProfileGroup4.name: usdPppProfileGroup4
usdPppProfileGroup4.description: A collection of objects providing management of profile functionality for PPP interfaces in a Unisphere product.
